        <h2>About the Editor</h2>
        <img src="john2.png" alt="John Shutt"></img>
        <p>
          My goal as an editor is to be honest, thorough, and specific. I work closely with authors to understand their goals and vision, and provide in-depth critical feedback that takes them seriously. That means no ego-stroking, no vague platitudes, and no canned responses&#8212;just the editing they need to make their writing the best it can be.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background is in literary fiction, but I have edited dozens of novels, novellas, and short stories in a variety of genres. I specialize in working with authors who are planning to e-publish their work. I have a degree in creative writing from Florida State University, where I took workshops with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Olen_Butler">Robert Olen Butler</a>, <a href="http://elizabethstuckeyfrench.com/">Elizabeth Stuckey-French</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Winegardner">Mark Winegardner</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>John Shutt currently lives in Philadelphia, where he is writing a novel.</em>
        </p>
